def: Pertaining to fields or the country, in opposition to the city;rural; rustic; unpolished; uncouth. "Agrestic behavior." Gregory.

The dense tissues which invest the teeth, and cover theadjacent parts of the jaws. Gum rash (Med.), strophulus in a teethingchild; red gum.-- Gum stick, a smooth hard substance for children to bite uponwhile teething.
Paleness produced by absence of light, or by disease.Dunglison.
One of the oxides of manganese; -- called also gray manganeseore. It occurs in brilliant steel-gray or iron-black crystals, alsomassive.

Of or pertaining to an era marked by early stone implements.The Paleolithic era (as proposed by Lubbock) includes the earlierhalf of the "Stone Age;" the remains belonging to it are for the mostpart of extinct animals, with relics of human beings.
Tending or adapted to remind; careful to remind. Southey.
